  "prompt": "How does hydraulic car parking work?",
  "response": "Hydraulic car parking systems, also known as hydraulic lifts or car stackers, work using the principles of hydraulics to vertically stack and store vehicles in a compact space. Here's a basic overview of how they function:\n\n1. Basic Components:\n- Hydraulic cylinders\n- Platforms or lifts\n- Control system\n- Structural frame\n\n2. Operational Principle:\n- Hydraulic fluid (usually oil) is pressurized in cylinders\n- Pressure creates force that raises or lowers platforms\n- Platforms can move vertically and sometimes horizontally\n\n3. Parking Process:\n- Vehicle drives onto the bottom platform\n- Hydraulic system lifts the platform and vehicle\n- Platform moves up or down to designated parking spot\n- Additional platforms can be stacked vertically\n\n4. Types of Systems:\n- Simple two-level lifts\n- Multi-level parking systems\n- Automated parking systems with computer control\n- Rotary or puzzle-type parking solutions\n\n5. Advantages:\n- Maximizes parking space\n- Reduces land usage\n- Allows vertical vehicle storage\n- Can be used in urban areas with limited parking\n\nThe specific design and complexity can vary depending on the specific hydraulic parking system's purpose and location.",
